I would like to express my feedback for the on-road assistance I received for my Tata Nexon EV (regi - MH02GB6051 under the name of my father, Dr. Sanjay Bagadia) which showed an EV Critical System Alert message since like 2 days (now awaiting resolution). 
The situation when called on the RSA number was very promptly handled by Mr. Mohammed Navas, with constant follow-ups the whole day since like 1:30PM in the afternoon to 8:30PM, kudos to that and thank you!! 

My major concern is now with the on-ground network of towing services because of which I had go through such a long ordeal. There was absolutely no tow truck for 5 hours in a busy city like Mumbai. 
Secondly, software issues of the car itself. Since the date of purchase, despite regular servicing, the car constantly brings up some or the other software bug while driving (braking and regen issues being the riskiest, and the hanging and intermittent disconnection of the infotainment system) and as is the case with such issues, they appear, disappear and re-appear in no specific pattern. I cannot be hanging on this unpredictability of such bugs when driving an electric vehicle with the added issue of range anxiety. 
I hope you look into these issues at the earliest. 

Thanks, and please convey my gratitude to Mr. Mohammed Navas too.
